# supabase/functions/.env.example
#
# SERVER-ONLY environment variables (CLAUDE.md §3, docs/06 §9, docs/08 §5). These
# are read either by code under supabase/functions/ or by Supabase Auth via
# config.toml env() substitution (the Google OAuth block below) — none of them may
# appear in apps/* or packages/*. The Phase-0 CI guard (scripts/check-secrets.sh)
# blocks the provider-key and service-role-key value patterns from being committed
# under client code.
#
# Local dev: copy to `supabase/functions/.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in
# real values. `supabase functions serve` picks them up automatically.

# --- Supabase platform -----------------------------------------------------
# Local: from `supabase status` (api URL and the service_role JWT).
# Hosted: pre-populated by the Supabase platform — do NOT override.
SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=replace-with-anon-key-from-supabase-status
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=replace-with-service-role-key-from-supabase-status

# --- Provider (Google Places, Phase 2) -------------------------------------
# Get a key from a Google Cloud project that has Places API (New) enabled. This
# is the ONLY place the key may live (CLAUDE.md §2.1, §3) — it is read only by
# supabase/functions/_shared/provider/google-places.ts. NEVER paste it into
# apps/*.env*, packages/*, or any client-bundled code.
PROVIDER_GOOGLE_API_KEY=replace-with-google-places-api-key

# --- Auth: Google OAuth provider (Phase 4.5) -------------------------------
# Credentials for the "Continue with Google" sign-in. Consumed by Supabase Auth
# through config.toml [auth.external.google] env() substitution — NOT by Edge
# Function code, and NOT by the apps (which only read the public anon key + URL,
# CLAUDE.md §3). Real values are local/dev only and must never be committed; keep
# them in supabase/functions/.env.local (gitignored).
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=replace-with-google-oauth-client-id
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_SECRET=replace-with-google-oauth-client-secret

# --- Provider selection (TESTS ONLY) ---------------------------------------
# PROVIDER selects the RestaurantProvider in getProvider() (_shared/provider/index.ts).
# Leave UNSET in any deployed env so the real GooglePlacesProvider is always used.
# Set to `fake` ONLY for the local Prompt-7 integration tests — it swaps in the
# deterministic FakeProvider (fake-restaurants.json), so tests never hit the network
# or need a real provider key (CLAUDE.md §7). Both provider-touching functions
# (start-session and resolve-session's widen) read the same vars below. Example run:
#   supabase functions serve resolve-session --env-file supabase/functions/.env.test
# (with PROVIDER=fake set in that file).
# PROVIDER=fake
#
# PROVIDER_FAKE_THROW, when set with PROVIDER=fake, makes FakeProvider throw so the
# start_session / resolve_session PROVIDER_ERROR path can be exercised. Never in a deployed env.
# PROVIDER_FAKE_THROW=1
